{"id":"221226850_Support_Vector_Machines_on_GPU_with_Sparse_Matrix_Format","abstract":"Emerging general-purpose Graphics Processing Unit (GPU) provides a multi-core platform for wide applications, including machine learning algorithms. In this paper, we proposed several techniques to accelerate Support Vector Machines (SVM) on GPUs. Sparse matrix format is introduced into parallel SVM to achieve better performance. Experimental results show that the speedup of 55x-133.8x over LIBSVM can be achieved in training process on NVIDIA GeForce GTX470.","authors":["Tsung-Kai Lin","Shao-Yi Chien"],"meta":["December 2010","DOI:10.1109/ICMLA.2010.53","SourceDBLP","Conference: The Ninth International Conference on Machine Learning and Applications, ICMLA 2010, Washington, DC, USA, 12-14 December 2010"],"references":["267984826_The_sparse_matrix_vector_product_on_GPUs","234786663_Fast_Training_of_Support_Vector_Machines_Using_Sequential_Minimal_Optimization","221997121_Multi-Class_Support_Vector_Machine","221345076_Fast_support_vector_machine_training_and_classification_on_graphics_processors","3684535_Comparison_of_classifier_methods_a_case_study_in_handwritten_digit_recognition","3192276_Database_for_handwritten_text_recognition_research","2985446_Gradient-Based_Learning_Applied_to_Document_Recognition","2614456_Large_Margin_DAGs_for_Multiclass_Classification","322183010_Compute_Unified_Device_Architecture","307881957_LIBSVM_A_library_for_support_vector_machines","271513141_Support_Vector_Networks","262333164_Making_Large-Scale_Support_Vector_Machine_Learning_Practical","242453233_Another_approach_to_polychotomous_classification","228715647_LIBSVM_A_library_for_support_vector_machines","228680178_Efficient_Sparse_Matrix-Vector_Multiplication_on_CUDA","224581828_Benchmarking_GPUs_to_tune_dense_linear_algebra","220938894_Parallel_multiclass_classification_using_SVMs_on_GPUs","220343922_Support_Vector_Network","220320025_Working_Set_Selection_Using_Second_Order_Information_for_Tra